The paper deals with the problem of sparse representation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of bi-orthogonal dictionaries is a specific technique in linear algebra and numerical analysis (cs.NA), and the analysis of the performance of l1-reconstruction involves statistical inference (cs.SI).
